  "text": "The phylogenetic tree shows the B. taurus and B. indicus cattle breeds divided obviously into two large main groups. This finding has support from several studies carried out with either microsatellite or mtDNA [CITATION_1] [CITATION_2] . Native EAR and AB populations in this study occupied a position between breeds originated from Europe and Africa; the native TG and SAR populations fell closer to the European breeds analyzed. In considering distance values relative to European breeds, native breeds are ordered as AB, EAR, SAR, and TG, respectively. This finding may arise because of the AB and EAR populations having a larger expansion area in Anatolia, and thus far there have been no effective selection and crossbreeding studies in TG and SAR populations.",
